        <div class="episode-description mt-4">
            <p>Perhaps you have someone in your life who&rsquo;s prone to sports gambling. Michael Lewis has someone. So he comes up with a scheme to &ldquo;inoculate&rdquo; his 17-year-old son against the lure of placing bets online. All the while, Lewis tries to craft the perfect &ldquo;master class&rdquo; for would-be gamblers to understand the dangers of what they might be getting themselves into.</p> <p>Here's his reading list:</p> <p><a href="https://www.google.com/books/edition/The_Logic_of_Sports_Betting/y_c_xQEACAAJ?hl=en">The Logic of Sports Betting</a> by Matt Davidow and Ed Miller</p> <p>Stephen Pinker&rsquo;s <a href="https://stevenpinker.com/publications/rationality-what-it-why-it-seems-so-scarce-and-why-it-matters">Rationality: What It Is, Why It Seems Scarce, Why It Matters</a></p> <p><a href="https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/241363/weapons-of-math-destruction-by-cathy-oneil/">Weapons of Math Destruction</a> by Cathy O&rsquo;Neil</p> <p>&nbsp;</p><p>See <a href="https://omnystudio.com/listener">omnystudio.com/listener</a> for privacy information.</p>
